-- Harper Appoints Two Senators, Giving Conservatives Majority in Upper House
-- B y   A l e x a n d r e   D e s l o n g c h a m p s
-- 2010-12-20T19:45:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-20/harper-appoints-two-senators-giving-conservatives-majority-in-upper-house.html
Canadian Prime Minister Stephen
Harper today announced the appointment of two Conservative Party
supporters to the Senate, giving them an absolute majority in
the upper chamber.  Don Meredith, a reverend and the executive director of the
Toronto-region GTA Faith Alliance, and Larry Smith, former
commissionner of the Canadian Football League and the president
and chief executive officer of the Montreal Alouettes, will give
the Conservatives 54 seats out of 105 in the Senate.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexandre Deslongchamps in Ottawa at 
 adeslongcham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Badertscher at 
 pbadertscher@bloomberg.net  